# Git Branch & Commit Conventions

This project MUST show clean, incremental development history for the beecrowd/Winter
assessment. Use **one git branch per feature** and **incremental commits per phase**
inside that branch.

## Branch strategy (one branch per feature)

| Branch | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `master` | Stable baseline: spec-kit setup, specs, plans, tasks, README. Merge target after review. |
| `001-ai-order-engine` | Implementation of feature `specs/001-ai-order-engine/` (T001–T052). |

**Rules**:

- Create branch name from feature directory: `specs/<NNN-short-name>` → branch `<NNN-short-name>`.
- All **implementation code** (src/, prisma/, docker, tests) commits go on the feature branch.
- Do **not** mix two features on the same branch.
- When starting a new feature: `git checkout master && git pull && git checkout -b <NNN-short-name>`.
- After review: open PR `001-ai-order-engine` → `master` (or merge locally).

**Current feature branch**: `001-ai-order-engine` (active for implementation).

Spec-kit resolves the feature via `.specify/feature.json`, not branch name — but branch
and directory SHOULD match for easier code review.

## Commits per phase (inside the feature branch)

Never squash the entire implementation into one commit. Commit after each **checkpoint**
in `specs/001-ai-order-engine/tasks.md`.

- Commit only when the user explicitly asks (e.g. "commit T010-T011").
- After completing a checkpoint, suggest a commit on the **current feature branch**.
- One logical unit per commit: setup slice, schema, tests, service, routes, or docs.
- Do NOT commit unrelated phases together (e.g. orders API + AI chat in one commit).
- Verify branch before commit: `git branch --show-current` must be `001-ai-order-engine`
  during implementation (not `master`).

## Message format (Conventional Commits)

```text
<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary ≤72 chars>

Refs: T0XX[-T0YY]
```

**Types**: `feat` | `test` | `chore` | `docs` | `fix` | `refactor`

**Language**: English for commit subjects.

**Examples**:

```text
chore(setup): scaffold Next.js 15 App Router project
Refs: T001

feat(orders): implement POST and GET /api/orders endpoints
Refs: T025-T026

test(cancel): add integration tests for PENDING-only cancellation
Refs: T027-T028
```

## Suggested commit map (follow during implementation)

| Phase | Suggested commits | Tasks |
|-------|-------------------|-------|
| Setup | scaffold + deps; docker compose; assets + layout | T001-T009 |
| Foundational | prisma schema + migration; lib clients + lock; services skeleton + schema tests; instrumentation | T010-T019 |
| US1 | order tests; order service; order API routes | T020-T026 |
| US2 | cancel tests; cancel service + route | T027-T030 |
| US3 | batch tests; batch service + cron; trigger route + logging | T031-T037 |
| US4 | chat tool tests; KB + tools + agent; chat API + UI | T038-T045 |
| Polish | swagger asset; README SDD + GenAI; gitignore + validation fixes | T046-T052 |

Prefer **test commit before feat** when TDD applies (e.g. T020 before T022).

## Workflow summary

```text
master                    → docs, specs, constitution (planning artifacts)
  └── 001-ai-order-engine → T001..T052 implementation
        ├── commit (Phase 1 Setup)
        ├── commit (Phase 2 Foundational)
        ├── commit (US1) …
        └── PR → master
```

## Files to NEVER commit

`.env`, secrets, `node_modules/`, `.next/`, local IDE config with credentials.

## After committing

1. Run `git status` — working tree clean for the completed slice.
2. Confirm you are on the feature branch before starting the next phase.
